Reasoning: The paper focuses on improving end-user performance by dynamically tuning the network stack, which falls under the category of network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the potential security implications of tuning the network stack, which could fall under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel framework for dynamically tuning the network stack, which could fall under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) or systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper uses empirical evidence to demonstrate the effectiveness of their framework, which could fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
